    1.0 out of 5 starsConfused By the Back not Matching the Front on Button Down tie. What's up, or, should I say down?
    May 17, 2018
    Size: X-LongColor: Burgundy/Light Blue Dot (Contrast Tail: Stripes)Verified Purchase
    I purchased an identical tie and returned it and ended up receiving a tie with the same type of problem this second time. The back part of the tie is striped and the front part is dotted. I am surprised. Is it supposed to be that way? Originally, in the first shipment I received a blue patterned tie and the back part of that tie was of a matching pattern. This does not make sense.

    I would also note that the surface of the tie is what I called picky, meaning if I rub my thumb on it, the material seems to want to catch. That alone is not enough for me to buy the tie or give it one star. My main concern is the narrow part of the tie not matching the front, wider part.
